To find out how long James spends reading, we can set up a proportion. We know that it takes James 10 minutes to read 3 pages, so we can set up the proportion:

\frac{10 \text{ minutes}}{3 \text{ pages}} = \frac{x \text{ minutes}}{18 \text{ pages}}

To solve for x, we can cross multiply:

10 \text{ minutes} \cdot 18 \text{ pages} = 3 \text{ pages} \cdot x \text{ minutes}

180 \text{ minutes} = 3 \text{ pages} \cdot x \text{ minutes}

Dividing both sides by 3 pages gives us:

x \text{ minutes} = \frac{180 \text{ minutes}}{3 \text{ pages}}

Simplifying, we find:

x \text{ minutes} = 60 \text{ minutes}

Therefore, James spends 60 minutes reading. 

